<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON EFA-12 - INSTALL/ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL/ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc id="hl0200604" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="13">
            <title>STEERING KNUCKLE ASSEMBLY</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Replace knuckle pin if pin finish is damaged. Always replace pin and bushings when either are
                        faulty.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the thrust bearing areas of the steering knuckle, the axle end, and
                    the knuckle pin bore of the axle beam (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200634">Figure 34</hotlnk>). Also pack dimples in bushing bores with grease.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200634" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200634.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 34. Lubrication</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position thrust bearing on knuckle with seal facing up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200635">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200635" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200635.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 35. Seal Facing Up</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount this assembly on axle beam.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wedge up steering knuckle and fill gap (at knuckle upper end) with shim or shims (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200636">Figure 36</hotlnk>). This is a pre-adjustment of knuckle vertical play.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200636" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200636.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 36. Install Shim or Shims</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position knuckle pin with flat aligned with draw key hole and start installing pin by
                    hand (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200637">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200637" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200637.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 37. Start Installing Pin by Hand</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install pin in knuckle and axle beam from the top. If necessary, tap pin in place using
                    hammer and brass drift (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200638">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200638" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200638.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 38. Install Pin in Knuckle</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>At this point in reassembly, check knuckle vertical play and adjust if necessary (see
                            Steps 7 through 10).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To check knuckle vertical play, center steering components.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount dial indicator to flange and reference top of knuckle pin. Zero dial indicator (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200639">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200639" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200639.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 39. Reference Dial Indicator</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Simulate axle loading with a jack (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200640">Figure 40</hotlnk>) and note dial indicator reading.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200640" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200640.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 40. Simulate Axle Loading</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Knuckle vertical play should be 0.002 inch to 0.012 inch (0.051 to 0.305 mm). Add or
                    remove shims as necessary to obtain correct end play.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With adjustment complete, check draw key opening and pin flat alignment (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200641">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200641" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200641.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 41. Check Draw Key Opening and Pin Flat Alignment</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new draw key (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200642">Figure 42</hotlnk>). Seat draw key with a hammer and punch.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200642" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200642.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 42. Install New Draw Key</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install draw key nut and tighten to 30 - 45 ft-lbs. (41 - 61 N&#183;m) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200643">Figure 43</hotlnk>). Reseat key and retorque nut.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200643" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200643.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 43. Tighten to Correct Torque</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install capscrews and lockwashers to secure cap (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200644">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200644" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200644.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 44. Install Cap</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten capscrews to 22 - 28 ft-lbs. (30 - 38 Nm) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200645">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200645" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200645.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 45. Tighten Capscrews</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach drag link to steering arm. Install and tighten nut to 165-230 ft-lbs. (224-312 N&#183;m).
                    Also see NOTE below. Install cotter pin.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach tie rod end to Ackermann Arm. Install and tighten to 165 - 230 ft-lbs. (224 - 312
                    N&#183;m)* (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200646">Figure 46</hotlnk>). Install cotter pin.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200646" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/g0200646.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 46. Install Tie Rod End</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>*Tighten nut to range minimum, then tighten further to align cotter pin hole. Check to make
                        sure torque does not exceed range maximum. If it does, use a new nut.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
